title:
SLOW COOKER SHREDDED CHICKEN TACOS
YIELD: 12 TACOS PREP TIME: 5 MIN
directions: Place chicken, taco seasoning, ranch powder, and tomatoes into a slow cooker. Cover and cook on high for 3-4 hours or low for 5-8 hours or until meat is easily shred with a fork.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Arrange taco shells in a 9x13 baking dish. Depending on the shells, you may need to use two pans.
Spoon meat into taco shells and top with cheese.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with diced cilantro and drizzle with hot sauce or taco sauce.
ingredients: 1/4 cup hot sauce or taco sauce
